<br>
Fenula knelt beside the statue of Prexus, praying. The tiny chapel in the corner of the infirmary contained statues of all the gods, for none had dominion over healing, but the Ocean Lord took central place. Taneith waited quietly in the shadows until Fenula rose.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fenula. Perhaps I am speaking out of turn, but I am worried about Echtelion. He does not seem himself. Something ails him, something that is beyond my powers perhaps. And he is stubborn and pride and would not tell me about it an any case. Do you know of what I speak?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tanieth>Tanieth</A> at: 2/5/04 6:55 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47>Guilds and Associations</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3p<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

